            "textOriginal": "Silly suggestion that has stolen my sleep these last few days. For purely sportive reasons, not financial, I'm actually excited about a European continental league with all the greatest teams from 150 years of association football tradition duking it out every year. Fuck the money. The teams still have to bloody qualify, they must be promoted as well as relegated. Sport is first, money second, the American solution ain’t gonna work on the European continent. Sure, money is a very practical sociological toolbut it turns people into tools, some things are Olympian and above money. (Sorry, gotta breathe…)\n\nAnyway, here's my attempt at what the ESL setup should have been, if money hadn't blinded the sheiks:\n\nA new continental league (NCL?), under UEFA, will replace the current CL, playing for the same Big Ears trophy to continue its history. Fuck it, keep calling it Champions League, now it’s just an actual annual league. This new league will then be the only league tournament these teams play that season (!), after they’ve qualified. Teams are still on for the FA Cup, Copa del Rey, national team cups, etc.\n\nThe European football continent is divided into 10 tiers, with current national leagues acting as qualification for the NCL and/or the playoffs. You could go only by regionbut I also believe that a few national leagues will need to be their own tier due to their established history. Everybody has their national pridebut sportively, some leagues have ended up standing out in the football world, what can you do?\n\nOwn tier: The English Premier League (4 teams in NCL)\n\nOwn tier: The Spanish Liga (4 teams in NCL)\n\nOwn tier: The Italian Serie A (4 teams in NCL)\n\nOwn tier: The German Bundesliga (4 teams in NCL)\n\nTier, Celtic Europe: (2 teams in NCL)\nNorthern Ireland\nRepublic of Ireland\nScotland\nWales\n\nTier, Western Europe: (4 teams in NCL)\nFrench Ligue 1\nDutch First Division\nBelgian First League\nPortuguese First Division\nAndorra\nGibraltar\nLuxembourg\n\nTier, Northern Europe: (2 teams in NCL)\nDenmark\nFaroe Islands\nFinland\nIceland\nNorway\nSweden\n\nTier, Central Europe: (2 teams in NCL)\nAustrian Bundesliga\nCzech Republic\nHungary\nLiechtenstein\nPoland\nSan Marino\nSlovakia\nSwitzerland\n\nTier, Southern Europe: (3 teams in NCL)\nArmenia\nAzerbaijan\nGeorgia\nGreece\nTurkey\nAlbania\nBosnia and Herzegovina\nBulgaria\nCroatia\nCyprus\nIsrael\nMalta\nKosovo\nMontenegro\nNorth Macedonia\nRomania\nSerbia\nSlovenia\n\nTier, Eastern Europe: (3 teams in NCL)\nRussian Premier League\nUkrainian Premier League\nBelarus\nEstonia\nKazakhstan\nLatvia\nLithuania\nMoldova\n\nAt the beginning of each season, each tier has a playoff tournament maybe two, four weeks long, maybe more.
